00:28:33,258 --> 00:28:35,123
Go to the--

244
00:28:35,193 --> 00:28:37,457
- that would be wonderful.
- In my office.

245
00:28:37,529 --> 00:28:40,589
- And how long do you think
that will take ?
- [ Chuckles ]

246
00:28:40,665 --> 00:28:42,929
Well, uh,

247
00:28:44,736 --> 00:28:47,170
I'll be expecting
your call.

248
00:28:47,239 --> 00:28:49,332
Thank you.

249
00:29:04,890 --> 00:29:07,188
To repeat, CNN has confirmed
the detonation of
a nuclear device in Europe.

250
00:29:07,259 --> 00:29:10,194
[ Overlapping Chatter ]

251
00:29:10,262 --> 00:29:13,663
[ Kelly ] We got confirmation.
There were ten warheads on that train.

252
00:29:13,732 --> 00:29:16,997
- Departure orders. Forty men on board.
- This is meaningless.

253
00:29:17,069 --> 00:29:19,003
- It's in Russian.
- [ Speaking Russian ]

254
00:29:22,574 --> 00:29:24,508
[ Speaking Russian ]

255
00:29:25,811 --> 00:29:27,745
- Princeton.
- Mmm.

256
00:29:27,813 --> 00:29:29,781
The blue-blooded backbone
of our country.

257
00:29:29,848 --> 00:29:33,807
- My father's a mailman.
- Well, you'd never know.

258
00:29:33,885 --> 00:29:36,854
Ilin, Kodoroff, Kulik,
Levindovsky, Lu--

259
00:29:36,922 --> 00:29:41,359
- Kodoroff ? Aleksander Kodoroff ?
- Yeah. You know him ?

260
00:29:41,426 --> 00:29:43,860
Yeah, I know him.
Goddamn it !

261
00:29:43,929 --> 00:29:47,592
I don't know about the rest of these
guys, but General Aleksander Kodoroff...

262
00:29:47,666 --> 00:29:49,759
doesn't ride around on
a nuclear transport train.

263
00:29:49,835 --> 00:29:51,826
Get me N.M.C.C. Intel,
please.

264
00:29:51,903 --> 00:29:54,770
- It's like lvana Trump on a subway.
- Can you get my files ?

265
00:29:56,842 --> 00:29:59,777
- Have that enhanced off the Urals.
- [ Man ] Yes, sir.

266
00:29:59,845 --> 00:30:01,779
- Sergeant.
- Sir.

267
00:30:01,847 --> 00:30:06,045
We know Kodoroff's under
investigation for corruption,
probably gonna be indicted.

268
00:30:06,118 --> 00:30:08,643
Gave a speech nine days ago
in Saint Petersburg.

269
00:30:08,720 --> 00:30:12,383
Mostly nationalistic bluster,
bemoaning the loss of empire...

270
00:30:12,457 --> 00:30:14,789
- and unity of the Slavic peoples.
- Yeah, yeah.

271
00:30:14,860 --> 00:30:19,229
Family history, phone records,
bank statements.

272
00:30:19,297 --> 00:30:24,200
Urinalysis from a Moscow traffic stop
last month: .367.

273
00:30:24,269 --> 00:30:27,864
- I'm amazed he could turn the key.
- That's a few cocktails.

274
00:30:27,939 --> 00:30:29,998
Saw his dentist on Tuesday,

275
00:30:30,075 --> 00:30:32,543
had dinner with some
very attractive people on Friday.

276
00:30:32,611 --> 00:30:34,909
We haven't been able
to l.D. them yet.

277
00:30:34,980 --> 00:30:36,914
Jesus, Costello,
you're slippin'.

278
00:30:36,982 --> 00:30:40,315
- Oh, I'm gettin' old, sir.
- You're not old.

279
00:30:40,385 --> 00:30:42,649
General Garnett's old.
[ Chuckles ]

280
00:30:42,721 --> 00:30:45,690
If you don't mind me askin',
sir, is Kodoroff involved ?

281
00:30:45,757 --> 00:30:49,318
- We don't know. He was on the train.
- You see, that's funny.

282
00:30:49,394 --> 00:30:53,023
- Why's that ?
- Because the General's got
this Finnish mistress.

283
00:30:53,098 --> 00:30:55,362
- She lives in Helsinki.
- Laina.

284
00:30:55,433 --> 00:30:58,960
- Guy calls her every day
like clockwork. Never misses.
- So ?

285
00:30:59,037 --> 00:31:00,971
Well, the thing is,

286
00:31:01,039 --> 00:31:04,440
if this Kodoroff guy was on that train
and he's so dead,

287
00:31:04,509 --> 00:31:08,843
who's bouncin' calls to Laina
in Helsinki off some satellite
over southern Russia ?

288
00:31:11,016 --> 00:31:14,975
If that's a secure phone, I need it.
Excuse me, General.

289
00:31:15,053 --> 00:31:16,987
[ Dialing Phone ]

290
00:31:17,055 --> 00:31:19,580
Sir, if a top-ranking
Russian general is involved,

291
00:31:19,658 --> 00:31:23,617
any intel we get from Moscow
is either compromised--

292
00:31:23,695 --> 00:31:26,220
Palkawunic Vertikoff
Pajaloosta.

293
00:31:26,298 --> 00:31:28,766
- Or a flat-out lie.
- You're right.

294
00:31:28,833 --> 00:31:30,767
Dimitri, Tom Devoe.

295
00:31:30,835 --> 00:31:33,360
- What do you want ?
- Are you busy ?

296
00:31:33,438 --> 00:31:36,635
I'm with two women.
Call me back some other time.

297
00:31:36,708 --> 00:31:38,642
How're you guys
holdin' up ?

298
00:31:38,710 --> 00:31:41,941
I think the only virtue is,
people are forgetting Chechnya.

299
00:31:42,013 --> 00:31:45,779
[ Chuckles ] Yeah. Listen, D, I've got
the troop manifest from that train.

300
00:31:45,850 --> 00:31:49,479
Alek Kodoroff got vaporized
out there, did he ?

301
00:31:49,554 --> 00:31:53,490
- Yeah. What a shame.
- Yeah.

302
00:31:53,558 --> 00:31:58,018
So how is it he's calling Laina
from a bird over southern Russian ?

303
00:31:58,096 --> 00:32:00,291
How's he doin' that, D ?

304
00:32:04,636 --> 00:32:07,503
Hey, D,
are you still there ?

305
00:32:07,572 --> 00:32:09,506
You must be wrong
about that, Tom.

306
00:32:09,574 --> 00:32:14,136
Our figures indicate the fallout
should have dissipated by then.

307
00:32:14,212 --> 00:32:17,648
Let me fax you what we've got.
Your number ?

308
00:32:17,716 --> 00:32:20,412
Hold on. Fax number, please.
Hang on.

309
00:32:20,485 --> 00:32:23,386
[ Devoe ]
All right, 0-0-1-7-0-3...

310
00:32:23,455 --> 00:32:26,891
- 5-1-1-6-8.
- Six-eight.

311
00:32:26,958 --> 00:32:29,984
I'm going to hang up now.
Bye.

312
00:32:30,061 --> 00:32:32,359
Listen, D--

313
00:32:36,268 --> 00:32:38,327
That scared him.

314
00:32:42,207 --> 00:32:44,641
- Is this the fax ?
- Yes, sir.

315
00:32:49,781 --> 00:32:52,215
[ Newscaster ] lnformation
on the nuclear weapon incident...

316
00:32:52,284 --> 00:32:55,947
in Russia's Ural Mountains
is still sketchy at this hour,

317
00:32:56,021 --> 00:33:00,151
but we do have a few new facts
about the magnitude of the disaster.

318
00:33:00,225 --> 00:33:03,683
Seismographs around the world
detected the blast,

319
00:33:03,762 --> 00:33:07,493
and we have reports that the explosion
was seen as far away as Lithuania...

320
00:33:07,565 --> 00:33:09,590
on the Baltic Sea.

321
00:33:09,668 --> 00:33:12,102
Initial projections indicate
the nuclear fallout...

322
00:33:12,170 --> 00:33:15,731
will affect all of Russia
and northern Europe.

323
00:33:15,807 --> 00:33:17,741
There's still no word
on casualties.

324
00:33:17,809 --> 00:33:22,405
There's word that President
Clinton will issue a statement
on this tragedy in 30 minutes.

325
00:33:22,480 --> 00:33:24,539
Vienna, 2:00 p.m.,
Bacherplatz.

326
00:33:24,616 --> 00:33:26,948
Why Vienna ?

327
00:33:27,018 --> 00:33:29,384
- Kordech.
- Maybe.

328
00:33:29,454 --> 00:33:32,617
Kordech is a front for
the Russian mafia in Vienna.

329
00:33:32,691 --> 00:33:34,750
And it's
a trucking company.

330
00:33:34,826 --> 00:33:39,763
Whether it was an accident
or a deliberate act of terrorism
remains a question.

331
00:33:47,339 --> 00:33:50,797
I need NORAD's sector 9877
intel from the Urals,

332
00:33:50,875 --> 00:33:52,809
updated fallout patterns...

333
00:33:52,877 --> 00:33:55,641
and troop movements
from NATO humint.

334
00:33:55,714 --> 00:33:59,741
Honey-roasted. Think anybody'll mind
if I stole a couple of bags ?

335
00:33:59,818 --> 00:34:02,412
My old man will get a kick
out of the Executive Seal.

336
00:34:02,487 --> 00:34:04,819
Go ahead.
Knock yourself out.

337
00:34:04,889 --> 00:34:08,017
Would you call Langley ?
We're still waiting on the
psych profile on Kodoroff.

338
00:34:08,093 --> 00:34:10,527
He's an asshole.
I'll save you a trip.

339
00:34:10,595 --> 00:34:13,086
Thanks. I'll settle for
the official version.

340
00:34:13,164 --> 00:34:15,598
Okay. Officially,
he's an asshole.

341
00:34:15,667 --> 00:34:18,295
He'll do anything for money,
which is the good news,

342
00:34:18,370 --> 00:34:20,600
'cause it makes him
fairly predictable.

343
00:34:20,672 --> 00:34:23,266
I'd say he's been
anything but predictable.

344
00:34:23,341 --> 00:34:27,300
He took an order for an
expensive, hard-to-find product,

345
00:34:27,379 --> 00:34:29,370
and he intends to
make good on delivery.

346
00:34:29,447 --> 00:34:31,847
Supply and demand.

347
00:34:31,916 --> 00:34:35,079
Your area of expertise,
right, Colonel ?

348
00:34:35,153 --> 00:34:38,179
At least, that's
the word on the Hill.

349
00:34:39,691 --> 00:34:41,852
You've been
checkin' up on me.

350
00:34:41,926 --> 00:34:45,157
I like to know
who I'm working with.

351
00:34:49,934 --> 00:34:53,301
I'd like
to know something.

352
00:34:53,371 --> 00:34:57,205
You moved from Lawrence Livermore
to the White House.

353
00:34:57,275 --> 00:35:01,507
So, first you build the bombs
to blow up the entire world...

354
00:35:01,579 --> 00:35:04,241
and now you wanna
save it.

355
00:35:04,315 --> 00:35:06,408
Make up your mind.
Which is it gonna be ?

356
00:35:06,484 --> 00:35:10,682
Well, I believe
this week we're saving it.

357
00:35:10,755 --> 00:35:14,156
- [ Chuckles ]
- So, it's really that simple ?

358
00:35:14,225 --> 00:35:17,319
It is to me,
that simple.

359
00:35:17,395 --> 00:35:21,024
And when you've been the boss for more
than two weeks, you'll know that.

360
00:35:21,099 --> 00:35:26,230
Three weeks.
You've done some checkin' yourself.

361
00:35:26,304 --> 00:35:29,535
Well, I like to know
who I'm workin' with.

362
00:35:31,109 --> 00:35:34,806
Doctor, you can run your charts
and your theories all you want.

363
00:35:34,879 --> 00:35:37,439
In the field,
this is how it works.

364
00:35:37,515 --> 00:35:39,449
The good guys-- that's us--

365
00:35:39,517 --> 00:35:41,451
we chase the bad guys,
and they don't wear black hats.

366
00:35:41,519 --> 00:35:44,113
They are, however,
all alike.

367
00:35:44,189 --> 00:35:48,626
They demand power and respect,
and they're willing to pay
top dollar to get it.

368
00:35:48,693 --> 00:35:51,389
And that is our
highly motivated buyer.

369
00:35:51,463 --> 00:35:54,762
- What about other motivations ?
- Not important to me.

370
00:35:54,833 --> 00:35:56,926
Whether it's important to you or not,
there are people out there...

371
00:35:57,001 --> 00:36:00,129
who don't care about money
and don't give a damn about respect,

372
00:36:00,205 --> 00:36:02,867
people who believe the killing of
innocent men and women is justified.

373
00:36:02,941 --> 00:36:07,275
For them it is about rage,
frustration, hatred.

374
00:36:07,345 --> 00:36:09,643
They feel pain, and they're
determined to share it.

375
00:36:09,714 --> 00:36:12,877
That does me no good.
Now let's deal with the facts at hand.

376
00:36:12,951 --> 00:36:15,351
Twenty-three hours ago,
General Aleksander Kodoroff...

377
00:36:15,420 --> 00:36:18,116
stole ten nuclear warheads.

378
00:36:18,189 --> 00:36:21,317
He's just a delivery boy.

379
00:36:21,392 --> 00:36:26,159
I'm not afraid of the man who wants
ten nuclear weapons, Colonel.

380
00:36:26,231 --> 00:36:28,893
I'm terrified of the man
who only wants one.

381
00:36:30,468 --> 00:36:33,733
[ Children Shouting,
Chattering ln Serbian ]

382
00:36:46,885 --> 00:36:49,820
[ Chattering ln Serbian ]

383
00:37:26,457 --> 00:37:28,391
[ Speaking Serbian ]

384
00:38:32,223 --> 00:38:35,351
[ Phone Ringing ]

385
00:38:37,061 --> 00:38:39,154
[ Ringing ]

386
00:38:42,634 --> 00:38:45,228
[ Ringing ]

387
00:39:01,753 --> 00:39:05,018
[ Chattering ]

388
00:39:09,027 --> 00:39:11,860
[ Chuckling ]
Hey, look who's the secret agent.

389
00:39:11,929 --> 00:39:14,363
Nice hat. You don't
stand out at all.

390
00:39:14,432 --> 00:39:16,593
Dress shoes
with khakis ?

391
00:39:16,668 --> 00:39:19,535
- Look at you.
- Leave me alone.

392
00:39:19,604 --> 00:39:23,597
- Let me tell you:
whatever happens, deny it.
- I'll try that.

393
00:39:23,675 --> 00:39:26,200
These are CD's.
They are for Tasha.

394
00:39:26,277 --> 00:39:29,007
You will not like them.
How is she ?

395
00:39:29,080 --> 00:39:33,414
Sixteen, and in love with
a 20-year-old motocross racer.

396
00:39:33,484 --> 00:39:36,282
- She said to say hello.
- Send her my love.

397
00:39:36,354 --> 00:39:38,879
Is Kodoroff involved
with Kordech ?

398
00:39:38,956 --> 00:39:41,823
Dr. Julia Kelly,
Colonel Dimitri Vertikoff.

399
00:39:41,893 --> 00:39:45,260
- Dr. Kelly heads
the Nuclear Smuggling Group.
- With the White House.

400
00:39:53,271 --> 00:39:54,932
That's good.
That's good.

401
00:39:55,006 --> 00:39:57,566
I think we can do
business, Dr. Kelly.

402
00:39:57,642 --> 00:40:01,078
- Let's take a walk.
- Okay, let's take a walk.

403
00:40:03,614 --> 00:40:07,345
.. [ Woman Singing ln German ]

404
00:40:07,418 --> 00:40:09,852
[ Patrons Chattering ]

405
00:40:09,921 --> 00:40:13,982
[ Dimitri ] They sit here and drink.
We might as well join them.

406
00:40:14,058 --> 00:40:16,492
My group's been monitoring
Kordech for years,

407
00:40:16,561 --> 00:40:20,190
- but it's always been
a mafia/ex-K.G.B. operation.
- Until recently.

408
00:40:20,264 --> 00:40:23,597
You have to see that in
the context of my country.

409
00:40:23,668 --> 00:40:27,695
Alek Kodoroff comes from
a generation of officers who
grew up in a crumbling system.

410
00:40:27,772 --> 00:40:30,036
Those pictures in your head
about Russia--

411
00:40:30,108 --> 00:40:33,475
bread lines, shitty little apartments,
ancient cars--

412
00:40:33,544 --> 00:40:37,913
Kodoroff and his friends made sure
that it never applied to them.

413
00:40:37,982 --> 00:40:41,383
But now, even that system is crumbling.
[ Popping Sounds ]

414
00:40:41,452 --> 00:40:44,751
This was Kodoroff's way out,
his big score.

415
00:40:44,822 --> 00:40:47,814
So you brought us here because you
can't investigate Kordech yourself.

416
00:40:47,892 --> 00:40:51,487
No, no. I can't investigate
without alerting Kodoroff.

417
00:40:51,562 --> 00:40:53,996
Half the men
used to be in my unit.

418
00:40:55,666 --> 00:40:58,931
Mr. Dietrich Shumaker schedules
all Russian shipping for Kordech.

419
00:40:59,003 --> 00:41:01,938
- You have an appointment at 4:00.
- Good.

420
00:41:02,006 --> 00:41:04,736
- Let's go see a man about a truck.
- Cheers.

421
00:41:04,809 --> 00:41:08,370
[ Groans ]
That's gasoline.

422
00:41:08,446 --> 00:41:12,075
[ Chattering ]

423
00:41:12,150 --> 00:41:15,745
[ Horn Honking ]

424
00:41:26,864 --> 00:41:30,300
- Do you have them ?
- Yes. We have to begin immediately.

425
00:41:42,847 --> 00:41:45,281
[ Speaking Serbian ]

426
00:41:59,063 --> 00:42:01,657
You just have to remember the plan.
I'm Anthony Haden--

427
00:42:01,732 --> 00:42:03,597
- I'm Patty Carson.
- Right.

428
00:42:03,668 --> 00:42:06,637
We go in, we get the information
and then we get out.

429
00:42:06,704 --> 00:42:09,434
You call me Tony.
Here we go. Hi.

430
00:42:09,507 --> 00:42:12,840
I'm Anthony Haden.
This is my associate, Patty Carson.

431
00:42:12,910 --> 00:42:16,175
- I think Herr Shumaker's expecting us.
- Please follow me.

432
00:42:18,816 --> 00:42:22,252
[ Computer Beeping ]

433
00:42:24,722 --> 00:42:27,156
[ Receptionist ]
Make yourselves comfortable.

434
00:42:27,225 --> 00:42:29,159
Thank you.

435
00:42:31,429 --> 00:42:34,262
Trucking business
must be pretty good.

436
00:42:34,332 --> 00:42:37,529
Wonder what chateau in the Loire Valley
these came from.

437
00:42:37,602 --> 00:42:40,196
Mr. Haden ?
Welcome.

438
00:42:40,271 --> 00:42:42,205
Thank you very much
for seeing us.

439
00:42:42,273 --> 00:42:46,039
This is my associate,
Ms. Carson.

440
00:42:46,110 --> 00:42:49,944
-Nice place you have here.
-My personal taste runs to the ltalians,

441
00:42:50,014 --> 00:42:54,007
but the German and Austrian late Baroque
was heavily influenced by the ltalians.

442
00:42:54,085 --> 00:42:57,213
- Several of our paintings are ltalian.
- Mm-hmm.

443
00:42:57,288 --> 00:43:00,485
- That's a Tiepolo.
- Mm-hmm. Oh, yeah.

444
00:43:00,558 --> 00:43:06,292
I'm a big Leroy Neiman fan.
Are ya familiar at all with his work ?

445
00:43:06,364 --> 00:43:08,298
- No, I'm afraid not.
- No. Oh. Tsk.

446
00:43:08,366 --> 00:43:10,664
- Please, come in.
- Sure.

447
00:43:10,735 --> 00:43:12,703
To my office.

448
00:43:12,770 --> 00:43:16,137
- Oh, now, this is nice.
- Thank you.

449
00:43:16,207 --> 00:43:18,141
Have a seat.

450
00:43:20,711 --> 00:43:23,737
- How can we help you ?
- I just wanted some information...

451
00:43:23,814 --> 00:43:26,442
about, uh, trucking
in Russia.

452
00:43:26,517 --> 00:43:30,214
I might not be the right man
if you need to rent equipment.

453
00:43:30,288 --> 00:43:32,518
You're the head
of transportation, right ?

454
00:43:32,590 --> 00:43:34,990
The head ?

455
00:43:35,059 --> 00:43:37,254
- No, I just do the scheduling.
- Right.

456
00:43:37,328 --> 00:43:40,729
You're the guy who gets things done.
Smart. Put a German on it.

457
00:43:43,868 --> 00:43:46,063
Yes, well.

458
00:43:46,137 --> 00:43:50,733
- As I said, how can I help you ?
- What we wanna know is...

459
00:43:50,808 --> 00:43:54,710
if I wanted to rent a vehicle to steal
and transport nuclear weapons...

460
00:43:54,779 --> 00:43:57,543
from somewhere, let's say,
inside the Urals,

461
00:43:57,615 --> 00:44:00,743
would you be the guy
to talk to ?

462
00:44:06,691 --> 00:44:08,682
Would you be that guy ?

463
00:44:25,142 --> 00:44:27,235
No, I'm afraid not.

464
00:44:27,311 --> 00:44:29,779
I believe
our meeting is over.

465
00:44:30,848 --> 00:44:32,782
All right, well,
thank you for--

466
00:44:32,850 --> 00:44:35,478
- Do you like Ford Explorers ?
- We have to go, Mr. Haden.

467
00:44:35,553 --> 00:44:38,078
- Range Rovers, Land Cruisers ?
- We really have to go.

468
00:44:38,155 --> 00:44:41,124
- Mr. Haden, may I ask you
to leave the room ?
- [ Wrist Cracking ]

469
00:44:41,192 --> 00:44:44,252
- [ Kelly ] No ! No !
- Should've taken the money, Hans.

470
00:44:44,328 --> 00:44:46,387
[ Kelly Screaming ]

471
00:44:46,464 --> 00:44:49,763
- Get up and get behind that desk.
- You broke my nose.

472
00:44:49,834 --> 00:44:52,428
Not a word. Get the duct tape
out of my briefcase, now.

473
00:44:52,503 --> 00:44:56,200
I'm not gonna shoot you unless
I have to. If I have to, I'm
gonna feel real bad about it.

474
00:44:56,273 --> 00:44:58,935
- Now sit down. Give me the duct tape.
- Here.

475
00:45:11,088 --> 00:45:14,114
- I need the password.
What's the password ?
- Hang on.

476
00:45:14,191 --> 00:45:16,785
- The password.
- [ Gasping ] No.

477
00:45:16,861 --> 00:45:19,329
All right. Hang on.
All right, Hans.

478
00:45:19,397 --> 00:45:21,627
- Oh !
- We'll do it your way.

479
00:45:21,699 --> 00:45:24,600
How's the backhand ?
[ Cocking Gun ] Password.

480
00:45:26,337 --> 00:45:28,237
- Hasselhoff.
- Hasselhoff.

481
00:45:29,340 --> 00:45:33,140
How do you spell ''Hasselhoff'' ?
Come on.

482
00:45:33,210 --> 00:45:36,509
Way to go, Hans.
Very brave.

483
00:45:42,753 --> 00:45:45,688
- I'm in.
- [ Devoe ] All right, I need...

484
00:45:45,756 --> 00:45:49,055
the trucking invoices
for the last seven days.

485
00:45:49,126 --> 00:45:51,390
All right.

486
00:45:59,703 --> 00:46:02,900
[ Murmuring ]

487
00:46:02,973 --> 00:46:05,669
- This is your plan ?
- Yep.

488
00:46:05,743 --> 00:46:09,406
- This is your big plan ?
- This is my plan.

489
00:46:18,889 --> 00:46:21,653
[ Devoe ]
Let's go. Hurry up.

490
00:46:23,794 --> 00:46:26,991
- Let's go. Come on.
- Almost. Just logging off.

491
00:46:27,064 --> 00:46:30,329
- Stay on. Who cares ? Leave it on.
- Got it !

492
00:46:30,401 --> 00:46:32,892
Good.

493
00:46:32,970 --> 00:46:36,462
- [ Muttering ] Oh, shit.
- [ Chuckling ]

494
00:46:36,540 --> 00:46:39,509
All right.
Hang on. And...

495
00:46:39,577 --> 00:46:42,546
thank you very much,
Herr Shumaker.

496
00:46:49,920 --> 00:46:52,354
[ Beeping ]

497
00:46:55,092 --> 00:46:57,424
[ Speaking German ]

498
00:47:11,041 --> 00:47:13,305
- Go. Go !
- Come on ! Come on !

499
00:47:13,377 --> 00:47:15,311
Hurry !

500
00:47:22,119 --> 00:47:25,452
- You get it ?
- Got it. You all right ?

501
00:47:25,523 --> 00:47:30,426
- No, I'm not. Brilliant idea:
just smash his face in.
- That is how things get done.

502
00:47:30,494 --> 00:47:34,658
- That's thinking. No warning.
- A couple of bribes, it never
happened at all, right ?

503
00:47:34,732 --> 00:47:37,166
Check the seats.
They go all the way back.

504
00:47:37,234 --> 00:47:39,168
- Oh, yeah.
- Cool.

505
00:47:39,236 --> 00:47:42,637
- Embassy car.
- Of course. C.D. player,
bulletproof glass.

506
00:47:42,706 --> 00:47:45,470
Everything.
Oh, shit.

507
00:47:49,380 --> 00:47:51,348
We may have a problem.

508
00:47:51,415 --> 00:47:53,576
This is going to cost us.
What do you have ?

509
00:47:53,651 --> 00:47:56,518
- Eighty.
- That's enough. I'll be back.

510
00:47:58,589 --> 00:48:00,523
Hold this.

511
00:48:04,995 --> 00:48:08,192
- So you think he set us up ?
- Who ?

512
00:48:08,265 --> 00:48:11,860
- Your friend.
- No.

513
00:48:11,936 --> 00:48:14,131
How can you be
so sure ?

514
00:48:14,205 --> 00:48:16,435
Because he's my friend.

515
00:48:22,012 --> 00:48:24,810
- He needs more money. Give me.
- [ Gunshots ]

516
00:48:24,882 --> 00:48:27,112
- [ Gasping ]
- No !

517
00:48:27,184 --> 00:48:29,118
[ Kelly ]
Oh, my God ! Oh, my God !

518
00:48:30,454 --> 00:48:32,649
[ Devoe ]
Down !

519
00:48:32,723 --> 00:48:35,055
Out ! Out !

520
00:48:35,125 --> 00:48:37,150
[ Tires Squealing ]

521
00:48:41,765 --> 00:48:43,858
[ Gunshots Continue ]

522
00:48:45,269 --> 00:48:47,294
[ Click ]

523
00:49:06,724 --> 00:49:09,215
Get up front. Get up front !

524
00:49:09,293 --> 00:49:11,727
Up front ?

525
00:49:14,131 --> 00:49:17,066
- They're behind us.
- How many of them ?

526
00:49:17,134 --> 00:49:21,901
- Two. Two-- Three.
- Reach into that briefcase.
Pull out an extra magazine.

527
00:49:23,307 --> 00:49:26,276
[ Horn Honking ]

528
00:49:28,245 --> 00:49:30,338
- Where is it ?
- In the briefcase. Reach in !

529
00:49:30,414 --> 00:49:32,348
Goddamn it !

530
00:50:06,650 --> 00:50:09,642
Seat belt.

531
00:50:23,734 --> 00:50:25,998
No, don't !

532
00:51:04,908 --> 00:51:08,969
Come on. What's wrong with you ?
What's wrong with you ?

533
00:51:11,882 --> 00:51:15,374
What are you doing ?
Wait ! Shit.

534
00:51:15,452 --> 00:51:17,716
[ Pedestrians Screaming ]

535
00:52:02,099 --> 00:52:06,263
[ Engine Stalled ]

536
00:52:07,905 --> 00:52:09,770
[ Shouting ln German ]

537
00:52:12,476 --> 00:52:14,171
No ! No !

538
00:52:15,746 --> 00:52:18,340
[ Shouting ln German ]

539
00:52:23,620 --> 00:52:25,781
[ Gasping ]

540
00:53:04,361 --> 00:53:06,420
- Come on.
- The invoices.

541
00:53:06,497 --> 00:53:08,727
- Come on. Come on !
- The invoices !

542
00:53:08,799 --> 00:53:10,960
- Come on, goddamn it !
- No !

543
00:53:12,202 --> 00:53:14,136
Go, go, go ! Go !

544
00:54:24,908 --> 00:54:27,570
Dimitri has a...

545
00:54:27,644 --> 00:54:29,578
a daughter, Tasha.

546
00:54:30,681 --> 00:54:33,275
Sixteen.
She lives in Rybinsk.

547
00:54:37,087 --> 00:54:39,248
I remember
when she was three.

548
00:54:43,627 --> 00:54:47,256
Sh--
She's beautiful. Sh--

549
00:54:58,275 --> 00:55:00,243
Doesn't make sense, you know ?

550
00:55:00,310 --> 00:55:03,177
[ Sighs ]
You don't...

551
00:55:04,648 --> 00:55:06,582
kill a Dimitri Vertikoff.

552
00:55:06,650 --> 00:55:10,882
There are certain rules.
Killing him isn't useful.

553
00:55:12,856 --> 00:55:14,983
Is it ever ?

554
00:55:36,580 --> 00:55:38,912
I never watched
anybody die before.

555
00:55:53,263 --> 00:55:56,130
[ Beeping ]
Welcome. You've got mail.

556
00:55:56,199 --> 00:55:58,633
Oh.

557
00:55:58,702 --> 00:56:03,571
I e-mailed Shumaker's files to my
A.O.L. account before I logged off.

558
00:56:07,411 --> 00:56:09,345
Did it work ?

559
00:56:10,414 --> 00:56:14,441
Uh... yeah.

560
00:56:14,518 --> 00:56:18,750
We're looking for a vehicle hired
in the Urals on about June 29.

561
00:56:18,822 --> 00:56:20,756
- Right ?
- Yeah.

562
00:56:20,824 --> 00:56:24,453
- No, the truck's too small.
- Yeah, yeah. Saint Petersburg,
one direction.

563
00:56:24,528 --> 00:56:29,932
Point of origin: Chelyabinsk.
Registration number: 7056BM.

564
00:56:30,000 --> 00:56:32,491
Destination:
lmisli 44E.

565
00:56:32,569 --> 00:56:35,561
That's Azerbaijan.
It's just south of Russia.

566
00:56:36,740 --> 00:56:38,799
That's five miles
from fuckin' lran.

567
00:56:38,875 --> 00:56:41,400
Kodoroff crosses that border
and those nukes are gone.

568
00:56:41,478 --> 00:56:43,708
We got a payment number.
Looks like a bank-routing code.

569
00:56:43,780 --> 00:56:48,012
There's no names of any clients yet.
''44E.'' Does that mean anything to you ?

570
00:56:48,085 --> 00:56:51,282
- What ?
- Shumaker put a private memo
at the bottom of the invoice.

571
00:56:51,354 --> 00:56:54,187
- It can't be copied, and it
wouldn't show up in any--
- This is Devoe.

572
00:56:54,257 --> 00:56:56,725
We have a target vehicle.
It's a cargo truck.

573
00:56:56,793 --> 00:56:59,762
Registration:
7056 Bravo Mike.

574
00:56:59,830 --> 00:57:03,231
- It's traveling south from Chelyabinsk
to lmisli in Azerbaijan.
- 44E.

575
00:57:03,300 --> 00:57:06,565
I am requesting
a high-priority tasker.

576
00:57:06,636 --> 00:57:10,163
Any birds-- any birds--
find this truck.

577
00:57:10,240 --> 00:57:12,208
We've got nukes
heading for lran.

578
00:57:12,275 --> 00:57:15,836
What the hell is 44E ?

579
00:57:37,567 --> 00:57:41,264
[ Men Arguing ln Serbian ]

580
00:57:53,250 --> 00:57:55,184
[ Men Exclaiming ]

581
00:58:33,924 --> 00:58:36,017
- [ Speaking Serbian ]
- Da.

582
00:58:40,764 --> 00:58:44,200
I am a Serb.
I'm a Croat.

583
00:58:44,267 --> 00:58:46,201
I'm a Muslim.

584
00:58:47,771 --> 00:58:51,172
You will look at what
I have done and say,

585
00:58:51,241 --> 00:58:53,835
''Of course. Why not ?

586
00:58:53,910 --> 00:58:58,847
They are all animals. They have
slaughtered each other for centuries.''

587
00:58:58,915 --> 00:59:01,543
But the truth is...

588
00:59:01,618 --> 00:59:03,552
I am not a monster.

589
00:59:04,621 --> 00:59:07,852
I'm a human man.
I'm just like you...

590
00:59:08,925 --> 00:59:11,257
whether you like it or not.

591
00:59:11,328 --> 00:59:14,559
[ Soldiers Chattering,
Sergeant Shouting Drill ]

592
00:59:16,199 --> 00:59:18,258
Hey, Rich.
How you doing ?

593
00:59:18,335 --> 00:59:21,202
- We haven't seen you
since the great scud hunt !
- That's right.

594
00:59:21,271 --> 00:59:24,707
- Captain Santiago, sir.
- Hello, Captain.

595
00:59:24,774 --> 00:59:26,935
This is Lieutenant Beach.

596
00:59:27,010 --> 00:59:28,944
He'll be running the operation
from the ground, sir.

597
00:59:29,012 --> 00:59:32,072
- Gentlemen, tell me you found him.
- Damn close, sir.

598
00:59:32,148 --> 00:59:34,082
Giving them an average speed of
65 clicks,

599
00:59:34,150 --> 00:59:36,084
if their destination of lmisli
is correct...

600
00:59:36,152 --> 00:59:40,145
and if they're taking a direct
route, we've got 'em somewhere
about here, in Dagestan.

601
00:59:40,223 --> 00:59:43,249
Still in Russia, below Mahackala
on the Caspian Sea.

602
00:59:43,326 --> 00:59:46,523
We've snuck a peek at everything
within a 200-square-mile area.

603
00:59:46,596 --> 00:59:51,124
We haven't turned up your truck.
We think they're probably stuck
here, in Kumuh.

604
00:59:51,201 --> 00:59:54,898
- There's a hell of a
traffic jam down there, sir.
- Trucks are too close together.

605
00:59:54,971 --> 00:59:58,202
- We can't get an angle on the plates.
- What's going on down there ?

606
00:59:58,275 --> 01:00:01,267
Renewed fighting between
Armenia and Azerbaijan.

607
01:00:01,344 --> 01:00:04,245
Roads are clogged with refugees
fleeing north.

608
01:00:04,314 --> 01:00:09,217
Ken ? Ken ! Get me a copy
of Kodoroff's intel phone records.

609
01:00:09,286 --> 01:00:11,811
- What are you thinking ?
- I need an outside line here.

610
01:00:11,888 --> 01:00:14,516
Somebody give me
an outside line, please ?

611
01:00:27,137 --> 01:00:30,072
[ Horn Honking ]

612
01:00:31,274 --> 01:00:35,370
[ Speaking Russian ]

613
01:00:36,179 --> 01:00:38,113
Filthy fucking refugees.

614
01:00:38,181 --> 01:00:41,548
- Azerbaijani, Georgian, Kazhakstani.
- [ Honking Horn ]

615
01:00:42,886 --> 01:00:45,320
Eh, don't curse them.

616
01:00:45,388 --> 01:00:48,255
I don't care what bitch
gave birth to them--

617
01:00:48,325 --> 01:00:50,885
Moslem, Serb.

618
01:00:50,961 --> 01:00:53,589
I don't hate them
for who they are.

619
01:00:53,663 --> 01:00:55,961
I hate them
because they are poor.

620
01:00:56,032 --> 01:00:58,227
[ Car Phone Ringing ]

621
01:00:58,301 --> 01:01:00,394
[ Speaking Russian ]

622
01:01:03,373 --> 01:01:06,308
- [ Speaking Russian ]
- Hey, Alek, how's the ride down there ?

623
01:01:06,376 --> 01:01:09,834
- Who is this ?
- Doesn't traffic drive ya nuts
when you're in a hurry ?

624
01:01:09,913 --> 01:01:13,440
- Who the fuck is this ?
- It's Tom Devoe, Alek.
How the hell you been ?

625
01:01:13,516 --> 01:01:17,612
I gotta know. You still humpin' that
Finnish stewardess with the bad skin ?

626
01:01:17,687 --> 01:01:22,647
Tom. Are you still trading stolen cars
on the black market ?

627
01:01:24,794 --> 01:01:29,254
Hey, Alek, you watched CNN
during Desert Storm.

628
01:01:29,332 --> 01:01:33,200
Remember all those television shots from
the nose cone of the G.B.U. missiles...

629
01:01:33,269 --> 01:01:36,432
slammin' into those trucks ?

630
01:01:36,506 --> 01:01:38,440
Remember
that picture ?

631
01:01:38,508 --> 01:01:41,739
How it kept gettin' closer
and bigger on the screen ?

632
01:01:41,811 --> 01:01:45,747
You could just about see the faces
of those drivers, and then...

633
01:01:45,815 --> 01:01:50,548
zap, the picture went dead; we didn't
get to see what happened next.

634
01:01:50,620 --> 01:01:52,554
Well, guess what, Alek.

635
01:01:54,090 --> 01:01:56,285
You will,
you son of a bitch.

636
01:01:57,927 --> 01:02:01,727
Shit. Get out of the way.
[ Honking Horn ]

637
01:02:02,866 --> 01:02:05,426
[ Horn Honking ]

638
01:02:05,502 --> 01:02:09,097
- [ Beeping ]
- I guess that upset him.

639
01:02:09,172 --> 01:02:11,106
- Can you get an angle ?
- In a minute.

640
01:02:11,174 --> 01:02:14,109
He rear-ends some guy, that can't
detonate that nuke, can it ?

641
01:02:14,177 --> 01:02:16,543
- As long as no one opens
the primary, they're safe.
- Come on.

642
01:02:22,719 --> 01:02:26,211
Come on, sweetie.
Come on.

643
01:02:26,289 --> 01:02:28,223
It's coming.

644
01:02:31,194 --> 01:02:35,563
- 70-56 Bravo Mike. That's it.
- How long until the satellite
passes out of range ?

645
01:02:35,632 --> 01:02:38,328
- One hour, 46 minutes.
- Get in contact with Russian command.

646
01:02:38,401 --> 01:02:40,335
Give them the exact location
of the truck. Ken ?

647
01:02:40,403 --> 01:02:42,371
Boom.

648
01:03:35,125 --> 01:03:38,959
- We have to go now.
- We only have them under
surveillance for another hour.

649
01:03:39,028 --> 01:03:43,089
- It doesn't matter what the
State Department says, sir.
- Yes, sir, absolutely.

650
01:03:43,166 --> 01:03:45,999
- No, I understand, sir.
- Fine. Thank you.

651
01:03:46,069 --> 01:03:48,435
- Yes. Yes, sir. Will do.
- Thank you, sir.

652
01:03:49,906 --> 01:03:52,397
- Okay, go. You go.
- No, no, you go first.

653
01:03:52,475 --> 01:03:54,409
I was talkin' to the chairman
of the Joint Chiefs.

654
01:03:54,477 --> 01:03:56,536
He says the State Department
is draggin' their feet.

655
01:03:56,613 --> 01:03:58,774
I was talking to the president.

656
01:03:58,848 --> 01:04:03,012
- He says it's a Russian problem;
they have to manage it.
- No, we have the advantage now !

657
01:04:03,086 --> 01:04:05,452
The Russians say
they are handling this.

658
01:04:05,522 --> 01:04:08,491
The Russians couldn't find snow
in the middle of fuckin' winter.

659
01:04:08,558 --> 01:04:12,619
When that satellite is out of range,
those nukes are gone.

660
01:04:16,466 --> 01:04:18,457
It's only jet fuel.

661
01:04:21,471 --> 01:04:24,269
- Get up into NATO.
- Good for you. Let's go. Rich ?

662
01:04:24,340 --> 01:04:27,309
- No, wait. Wait. Colonel.
- Santiago !

663
01:04:27,377 --> 01:04:29,311
With Russia insisting they're
handling this,

664
01:04:29,379 --> 01:04:31,347
you will not take action
without authorization.

665
01:04:31,414 --> 01:04:34,110
What do you think I am, some
gung-ho stupid son of a bitch ?

666
01:04:34,184 --> 01:04:36,152
No, I don't think you're stupid.

667
01:04:36,219 --> 01:04:38,915
I think you're a talented soldier
with sloppy impulse control,

668
01:04:38,988 --> 01:04:42,446
and I don't want you provoking
an international incident
because of a personal agenda.

669
01:04:42,525 --> 01:04:45,494
My personal agenda
is my business.

670
01:04:45,562 --> 01:04:47,826
Now you are not
in Washington anymore.

671
01:04:47,897 --> 01:04:49,831
You are in the real world.
In the real world,

672
01:04:49,899 --> 01:04:52,299
there are nuclear arms
heading for lran.

673
01:04:52,368 --> 01:04:55,633
So whether you agree with me
or not, get me authorized !

674
01:05:32,342 --> 01:05:35,743
[ Speaking Serbian ]

675
01:05:59,802 --> 01:06:02,566
Cobra Three, this is Tango Six.
What have we got ?

676
01:06:02,639 --> 01:06:06,006
[ Kelly ] Russian command
has been notified of
the target vehicle's location.

677
01:06:06,075 --> 01:06:08,669
Proceed to position
and await further instructions.

678
01:06:08,745 --> 01:06:12,374
- Ken, does N.R.O. have
anything up there for us ?
- They got us on standby.

679
01:06:12,448 --> 01:06:14,416
Take this down.
How much time are we looking at ?

680
01:06:14,484 --> 01:06:16,475
We can track 'em for another
45 minutes.

681
01:06:16,552 --> 01:06:18,486
Let's alert IFOR
at the Bazta checkpoint.

682
01:06:18,554 --> 01:06:20,522
They'll have to pass
through there.

683
01:06:34,837 --> 01:06:36,771
Put that away.

684
01:06:37,974 --> 01:06:39,908
[ Speaking Russian ]

685
01:06:53,423 --> 01:06:56,153
[ Speaking Russian ]

686
01:07:54,250 --> 01:07:56,184
Stop.

687
01:07:58,054 --> 01:08:01,615
[ Soldier Speaking Russian ]

688
01:08:22,645 --> 01:08:26,046
[ Reporter ] There's been a tragic
setback in the ongoing effort...

689
01:08:26,115 --> 01:08:29,448
to secure lasting peace
in the former Yugoslavia.

690
01:08:29,519 --> 01:08:31,919
So far, no one
has taken responsibility...

691
01:08:31,988 --> 01:08:36,118
for the killing of the Bosnian-Serb
finance minister, Zarko Preljevich,

692
01:08:36,192 --> 01:08:39,184
who was assassinated
in a Sarajevo churchyard.

693
01:08:39,262 --> 01:08:41,560
Word of Preljevich's
violent death...

694
01:08:41,631 --> 01:08:44,725
has sent shock waves through
the international community.

695
01:08:44,801 --> 01:08:47,531
The well-liked moderate
was considered a crucial player...

696
01:08:47,603 --> 01:08:51,505
in the upcoming peace talke scheduled
to begin this week in New York.

697
01:08:51,574 --> 01:08:56,409
Reporting live from Sarajevo,
this is Jean Rogers for CNN.

698
01:08:58,247 --> 01:09:00,374
Forty-four ''E.''

699
01:09:01,951 --> 01:09:05,148
Forty-fourth parallel
runs through...

700
01:09:09,425 --> 01:09:11,359
Sarajevo.

701
01:09:13,863 --> 01:09:17,060
Where's that bank routing number ?
The one off the Kordech invoice ?

702
01:09:17,133 --> 01:09:20,068
- You better get over here.
- Check it against banks in Sarajevo.

703
01:09:20,136 --> 01:09:22,627
- What's going on ?
- A Russian roadblock.

704
01:09:22,705 --> 01:09:24,639
They're all dead, ma'am.

705
01:09:24,707 --> 01:09:26,937
I think
they're all dead.

706
01:09:27,009 --> 01:09:29,842
[ Devoe ]
Cobra Three, they got 'em ?

707
01:09:30,179 --> 01:09:32,977
Negative, Tango Six. How much longer
do we have them on satellite ?

708
01:09:33,049 --> 01:09:34,983
Less than ten minutes.

709
01:09:35,051 --> 01:09:36,985
Alert the Russians
of the truck's current position.

710
01:09:37,053 --> 01:09:39,021
Tell them they have
men down out there.

711
01:09:39,088 --> 01:09:42,956
Wallace, stand by to track
if they go to Bravo.

712
01:09:43,025 --> 01:09:47,291
[ Devoe ] We've now reached
the Federation airspace, Cobra Three.

713
01:09:47,363 --> 01:09:50,560
Running out of time.
Suggest we go.

714
01:09:50,633 --> 01:09:53,534
Negative, Six.
Do not proceed without authorization.

715
01:09:53,603 --> 01:09:56,094
- Do the Russians have
troops in the area ?
- Negative.

716
01:09:56,172 --> 01:09:58,732
[ Devoe ] Cobra Three, we're gonna
lose 'em on satellite. We have to go.

717
01:09:58,808 --> 01:10:01,709
Get me a secure phone link
to N.M.C.C. Negative, Six.

718
01:10:01,777 --> 01:10:05,577
Do not proceed without authorization.
You will not proceed.

719
01:10:09,819 --> 01:10:12,481
When we lose the satellite,
do we have other eyes in the area ?

720
01:10:12,555 --> 01:10:16,685
[ Kelly ] Sir, we have the target
vehicle approaching the lranian border.

721
01:10:16,759 --> 01:10:20,251
Requesting permission to enter Russian
Federation airspace and take it out.

722
01:10:20,329 --> 01:10:24,197
Dr. Kelly, in your estimation, is this
our only remaining course of action ?

723
01:10:24,267 --> 01:10:27,031
Based on available intel, the Russians
having no forces in place,

724
01:10:27,103 --> 01:10:29,367
our analysis of
the satellite sigint--

725
01:10:29,438 --> 01:10:34,705
I'm not asking for analysis, Dr. Kelly.
I'm asking for a decision.

726
01:10:34,777 --> 01:10:39,146
- Must advise we go, sir.
- Dr. Kelly, if there are
nuclear weapons on that truck,

727
01:10:39,215 --> 01:10:41,706
and the Russians
can't interdict,

728
01:10:41,784 --> 01:10:45,618
are you willing to risk a war
to stop it ?

729
01:10:48,691 --> 01:10:50,682
Yes, sir.

730
01:10:50,760 --> 01:10:52,955
Yes, sir, I am.

731
01:10:53,029 --> 01:10:56,157
Six, this is Cobra Three.
We have a go.

732
01:10:56,232 --> 01:10:58,598
Avoid foreign casualties.
Secure the target vehicle.

733
01:10:58,668 --> 01:11:00,898
Detain anyone found inside.

734
01:11:00,970 --> 01:11:05,566
Copy, Cobra. Six to task force.
We're cleared as briefed.
Let's rock and roll !

735
01:11:05,641 --> 01:11:09,407
This is Red Dog Pack to Three.
Execute. Execute.

736
01:11:27,897 --> 01:11:29,922
Why aren't they finished
back there ?

737
01:11:31,000 --> 01:11:34,458
[ Speaking Russian ]

738
01:11:44,080 --> 01:11:46,844
[ Speaking Russian ]

739
01:12:07,870 --> 01:12:11,636
Russian control tower,
this is Air Force 53762,

740
01:12:11,707 --> 01:12:17,202
a flight of three U.S. Air Force
helicopters in pursuit
of stolen nuclear weapons.

741
01:12:17,279 --> 01:12:19,270
Request a weapons-hold status.

742
01:12:19,348 --> 01:12:21,316
[ Speaking Russian ]

743
01:12:35,665 --> 01:12:38,793
You must return to Turkish airspace,
U.S. Air Force.

744
01:12:38,868 --> 01:12:42,429
Your intrusion is not authorized.
You have crossed international line.

745
01:12:48,010 --> 01:12:50,501
They've locked onto us.

746
01:12:51,681 --> 01:12:53,808
A second battery's
locked onto us.

747
01:12:59,055 --> 01:13:04,322
This is Air Force 53762. We are
in pursuit of stolen nuclear weapons...

748
01:13:04,393 --> 01:13:06,588
on their way to lran.

749
01:13:06,662 --> 01:13:09,859
Repeat: Put your weapons
on hold.

750
01:13:14,270 --> 01:13:17,535
Reverse course immediately,
or we will begin to fire.

751
01:13:17,606 --> 01:13:20,439
This is Red Dog Three.
We're lit up like a Christmas tree.

752
01:13:20,509 --> 01:13:23,603
This is Air Force 53762.

753
01:13:23,679 --> 01:13:26,113
Those weapons could be going to
Chechnya or Georgia.

754
01:13:26,182 --> 01:13:28,446
We repeat:
Put your weapons on hold !

755
01:13:28,517 --> 01:13:31,953
[ Speaking Russian ]

756
01:13:48,971 --> 01:13:50,871
Here they come !

757
01:13:54,977 --> 01:13:57,969
[ Devoe ] Number One is down.
Cobra, we have a downed aircraft...

758
01:13:58,047 --> 01:13:59,981
two miles east
of checkpoint four.

759
01:14:00,049 --> 01:14:03,416
- Number Three, acknowledge.
- This is Red Dog Three.

760
01:14:03,486 --> 01:14:05,977
Do you see the aircraft ?
Do you see any survivors ?

761
01:14:06,055 --> 01:14:08,785
Negative. The whole fucking forest
is up in flames.

762
01:14:08,858 --> 01:14:12,919
Number Three, duck behind the hill.
Behind the hill.

763
01:14:16,665 --> 01:14:19,657
- How many men on that chopper ?
- Nine.

764
01:14:24,340 --> 01:14:26,672
[ Devoe ]
Cobra Three, we're out of range.

765
01:14:26,742 --> 01:14:28,676
Target is two miles out.

766
01:14:42,324 --> 01:14:44,258
Here it is.

767
01:14:55,604 --> 01:14:59,233
What's he doing ?

768
01:14:59,308 --> 01:15:03,210
- Will it work ?
- It can be activated by a single man...

769
01:15:03,279 --> 01:15:07,010
and will render a nuclear yield
of one to two kilotons.

770
01:15:07,082 --> 01:15:09,573
- Why is he doing that now ?
- Because that was the deal.

771
01:15:09,652 --> 01:15:12,416
One warhead for us, to do
with as we wish.

772
01:15:12,488 --> 01:15:14,422
After I get my money.

773
01:15:14,490 --> 01:15:16,754
Helicopters !

774
01:15:21,997 --> 01:15:26,866
All right, gentlemen, whatever you do,
do not shoot any civilians.

775
01:15:26,936 --> 01:15:28,870
Do you understand ?

776
01:15:33,242 --> 01:15:35,642
Amerikanski.

777
01:15:35,711 --> 01:15:38,612
[ Gunfire ]

778
01:15:54,763 --> 01:15:56,628
Take out the road !

779
01:17:02,431 --> 01:17:05,400
Rig me a heavy lift line !

780
01:17:07,069 --> 01:17:10,163
Those fuckers
you can shoot !

781
01:18:05,227 --> 01:18:07,252
Let's get him out !
Pull up !

782
01:18:25,748 --> 01:18:27,875
[ Screaming ]

783
01:18:30,753 --> 01:18:33,847
Where are they goin', Alek ?
Where are they goin' ?

784
01:18:33,922 --> 01:18:36,447
Fuck you !

785
01:18:41,697 --> 01:18:46,464
- Get it down ! Lower it !
- Heavy line ! Let's go !

786
01:18:49,104 --> 01:18:52,437
- Grab it and get out !
- Drop a cable ! Drop it !

787
01:18:52,508 --> 01:18:55,705
Bring it down !
More ! More !

788
01:19:00,416 --> 01:19:03,351
Come on ! Get on !
Hook on !

789
01:19:03,419 --> 01:19:05,387
[ Grunting ]

790
01:19:18,033 --> 01:19:21,025
- More !
- Lower it ! We gotta lower it !

791
01:19:41,990 --> 01:19:44,857
[ Shrieking ]

792
01:19:44,927 --> 01:19:46,519
Go !

793
01:20:19,928 --> 01:20:23,625
- [ Men Shouting ]
- We're clear ! We're clear !

794
01:20:23,699 --> 01:20:28,159
All right, sweep 'em. Open 'em up.
Let's go ! Let's go !

795
01:20:28,237 --> 01:20:31,900
- You all right, sir ?
- Yeah. Open 'em up. Let's go !

796
01:20:31,974 --> 01:20:35,205
[ Devoe ] Give me the radio.
Cobra Three, are you there ?

797
01:20:35,277 --> 01:20:37,438
Six, what happened ?

798
01:20:37,513 --> 01:20:41,313
One assault aircraft is gone.
Nine men are dead.

799
01:20:41,383 --> 01:20:44,648
- Santiago !
- Kodoroff is dead, and we have
recovered...

800
01:20:44,720 --> 01:20:46,745
- eight nuclear warheads...
- Someone's holding on over the side !

801
01:20:46,822 --> 01:20:49,416
- in their containers.
- That's not enough warheads.

802
01:20:49,491 --> 01:20:53,222
- What ?
- [ Kelly ]
That's not enough damn warheads.

803
01:20:53,295 --> 01:20:56,890
- For once, you could
say something nice.
- It was an SS18-- ten warheads.

804
01:20:56,965 --> 01:21:00,298
One detonated, eight with you.
That leaves one unaccounted for.

805
01:21:00,369 --> 01:21:03,634
Colonel Devoe ! There's
somebody alive down here !

806
01:21:03,705 --> 01:21:07,471
Hold on a minute.
Take this. Motherfuck.

807
01:21:07,543 --> 01:21:10,103
Goddamn it !

808
01:21:11,613 --> 01:21:13,547
We got a live one, Colonel.

809
01:21:16,985 --> 01:21:21,684
- Do you speak English ?
- Yes, l-- I went to Harvard.

810
01:21:21,757 --> 01:21:25,158
Go, Crimson !
Help me up, please.

811
01:21:25,227 --> 01:21:27,286
- Where's the other warhead ?
- Please, bring me up.

812
01:21:27,362 --> 01:21:32,823
Listen to me very carefully.
You are gonna die unless you
tell me where the warhead is.

813
01:21:32,901 --> 01:21:35,768
- I don't know. He took it. He's gone.
- Who ?

814
01:21:35,837 --> 01:21:39,329
I don't know his name ! He's, uh,
with the ones who arranged this !

815
01:21:39,408 --> 01:21:42,502
- Kodoroff ?
- No, Kodoroff just handled the money !

816
01:21:42,578 --> 01:21:44,512
It was the other one !

817
01:21:44,580 --> 01:21:48,676
He-He made me dismantle
the primary, make it mobile.

818
01:21:48,750 --> 01:21:53,949
- How ?
- It's in his backpack.
Help me up, please ?

819
01:22:06,034 --> 01:22:08,161
- I'm goin' back to the rig.
- Help me up.

820
01:22:08,237 --> 01:22:10,762
- Just hang on. We'll bring you up.
- Okay.

821
01:22:16,478 --> 01:22:20,642
Kelly ? A guy
got away with a bomb.

822
01:22:20,716 --> 01:22:24,174
[ Kelly ] Copy, Devoe.
All right, come on back.

823
01:22:30,225 --> 01:22:32,887
We got it. The bank account
on the Kordech invoice ?

824
01:22:32,961 --> 01:22:36,692
Registered to an address in Grbavica,
a Serbian suburb of Sarajevo.

825
01:22:36,765 --> 01:22:41,634
Good. Get this information to IFOR.
Tell them to proceed with caution.

826
01:22:54,383 --> 01:22:56,544
Where are you going ?

827
01:23:25,781 --> 01:23:27,806
- [ Boy Chattering ]
- [ Siren Wailing ]

828
01:23:30,319 --> 01:23:32,810
[ Horn Honking ]

829
01:23:40,896 --> 01:23:42,830
[ Speaking Polish ]

830
01:23:52,207 --> 01:23:55,643
[ Speaking Serbian ]

831
01:23:58,747 --> 01:24:01,113
Tsk.

832
01:24:57,172 --> 01:25:00,300
- Are you all right ?
- I've been better. How 'bout you ?

833
01:25:00,375 --> 01:25:05,506
I've been better. We traced the money
back to a man named Vlado Mirich.

834
01:25:05,580 --> 01:25:09,072
IFOR found a tape in his apartment.
They're uplinking it to us now.

835
01:25:09,151 --> 01:25:11,847
They say it has some sort
of terrorist message on it.

836
01:25:11,920 --> 01:25:14,286
Colonel, the guy you caught
is Dr. Amir Taraki.

837
01:25:14,356 --> 01:25:18,520
Pakistani. Ph.D. in astrophysics.
Educated at Harvard.

838
01:25:18,593 --> 01:25:21,756
That's right. We educated
half the world's terrorists.

839
01:25:21,830 --> 01:25:23,991
- You need to tell me
exactly what he said.
- All right.

840
01:25:24,065 --> 01:25:27,159
He removed the primary from the warhead,
and he put it in a backpack.

841
01:25:27,235 --> 01:25:29,169
The primary is packed
with plutonium.

842
01:25:29,237 --> 01:25:32,070
Detonated, it could still
take out ten city blocks...

843
01:25:32,140 --> 01:25:34,404
- IFOR tape is transmitting !
- and kill 100,000 people...

844
01:25:34,476 --> 01:25:36,967
in a densely populated area
like Sarajevo or Tuzla.

845
01:25:37,045 --> 01:25:40,811
[ Mirich ] You will look at what
I have done and say,

846
01:25:40,882 --> 01:25:42,816
''Of course. Why not ?

847
01:25:42,884 --> 01:25:45,409
''They are all animals.

848
01:25:45,487 --> 01:25:48,081
They have slaughtered
each other for centuries.''

849
01:25:49,458 --> 01:25:51,858
But the truth is...

850
01:25:51,927 --> 01:25:53,918
I'm not a monster.

851
01:25:53,995 --> 01:25:57,453
I'm a human man.
I'm just like you...

852
01:25:57,532 --> 01:25:59,591
whether you like it
or not.

853
01:25:59,668 --> 01:26:04,002
For years, we have tried
to live together...

854
01:26:04,072 --> 01:26:06,632
until a war
was waged on us.

855
01:26:07,809 --> 01:26:09,800
On all of us.

856
01:26:09,878 --> 01:26:13,871
A war waged by
our own leaders.

857
01:26:13,949 --> 01:26:16,247
[ Mirich On Videotape, Continuing ]
And who supplied...

858
01:26:16,318 --> 01:26:18,582
the Serb cluster bombs,

859
01:26:18,653 --> 01:26:20,621
the Croatian tanks,

860
01:26:20,689 --> 01:26:23,624
the Muslim artillery shells...

861
01:26:23,692 --> 01:26:26,388
that killed
our sons and daughters ?

862
01:26:26,461 --> 01:26:32,127
It was the governments of the West who
drew the boundaries of our countries--

863
01:26:32,200 --> 01:26:35,567
sometimes in ink,
sometimes in blood--

864
01:26:35,637 --> 01:26:37,867
the blood of our people,

865
01:26:37,939 --> 01:26:40,931
and now, you dispatch
your peacekeepers...

866
01:26:41,009 --> 01:26:45,070
to write
our destiny again.

867
01:26:45,146 --> 01:26:48,240
We can never accept this peace
that leaves us...

868
01:26:48,316 --> 01:26:50,944
with nothing but pain--

869
01:26:51,019 --> 01:26:55,786
pain the peacemakers
must be made to feel.

870
01:26:55,857 --> 01:26:58,257
Their wives,
their children,

871
01:26:58,326 --> 01:27:01,659
their houses
and churches.

872
01:27:01,730 --> 01:27:05,723
So now you know.
Now you must understand.

873
01:27:06,801 --> 01:27:11,602
Leave us to find
our own destiny.

874
01:27:11,673 --> 01:27:15,336
May God have mercy
on us all.

875
01:27:15,410 --> 01:27:18,971
- [ Click ]
- IFOR can shut down Bosnia. He's
never gonna get into Sarajevo.

876
01:27:19,047 --> 01:27:21,538
- He's never gonna get into Tuzla.
- He's not going there.

877
01:27:21,616 --> 01:27:25,052
We weren't meant to find this until
after he had detonated the bomb.

878
01:27:25,120 --> 01:27:27,782
Now, ''pain the peacemakers
must be made to feel.''

879
01:27:27,856 --> 01:27:32,190
The peacemakers aren't in Bosnia.
They're in Europe and the U.S.

880
01:27:32,260 --> 01:27:35,252
- They're signing a new treaty
this week, right ?
- Tomorrow at the U.N.

881
01:27:35,330 --> 01:27:38,595
- What is the address ?
- Over by the river, east side.

882
01:27:38,667 --> 01:27:42,103
Forty-fourth Street.
Forty-four ''E.''

883
01:27:45,073 --> 01:27:47,200
He's goin' to New York.

884
01:28:08,129 --> 01:28:11,462
- What've you got, Ken ?
- The only way we can
close the airport...

885
01:28:11,533 --> 01:28:13,797
is with a Federal Nuclear Emergency
Response Plan.

886
01:28:13,868 --> 01:28:16,894
- It has to come from her.
- All right. I'll give it to her.

887
01:28:41,062 --> 01:28:42,996
I wanted to know...

888
01:28:44,065 --> 01:28:45,999
who they were.

889
01:29:23,338 --> 01:29:25,272
Oh.

890
01:29:26,474 --> 01:29:28,339
All right.

891
01:29:29,544 --> 01:29:31,910
Secure line to N.M.C.C.

892
01:29:34,049 --> 01:29:37,746
This is Dr. Julia Kelly.
I am issuing a presidential directive...

893
01:29:37,819 --> 01:29:40,185
for a Federal
Nuclear Emergency Plan.

894
01:29:40,255 --> 01:29:42,815
We have a possible weapon
of mass destruction...

895
01:29:42,891 --> 01:29:46,952
coming into the United States by
unknown terrorist or terrorists.

896
01:30:07,749 --> 01:30:10,274
- Check in the rear.
- Yes, sir.

897
01:30:10,351 --> 01:30:14,082
Commencing diplomatic evacuation.
Perimeter is secure.

898
01:30:14,155 --> 01:30:17,022
Repeat:
Perimeter is secure.

899
01:30:17,092 --> 01:30:19,424
Ladies and gentlemen, may I
have your attention, please ?

900
01:30:19,494 --> 01:30:23,521
I'm with the U.N. We've been
informed of a serious threat
to the treaty signing.

901
01:30:23,598 --> 01:30:26,692
We have to get you off this plane
to insure your safety.

902
01:30:26,768 --> 01:30:29,236
If you would all please stand up now.
Everyone, stand up.

903
01:30:29,304 --> 01:30:31,795
Thank you.
Move to the exits...

904
01:30:31,873 --> 01:30:35,309
at the rear and front of the aircraft
in an orderly fashion.

905
01:31:01,736 --> 01:31:04,000
- Glad you could make it. Coffee ?
- No, thank you, sir.

906
01:31:04,072 --> 01:31:06,199
- I popped a couple of ''stay-awakes''
on the plane.
- Dr. Kelly ?

907
01:31:06,274 --> 01:31:09,243
- I'm fine.
- How many ''stay-awakes'' did she take ?

908
01:31:09,310 --> 01:31:11,642
This is Mark Carey, Energy.

909
01:31:11,713 --> 01:31:15,342
Over here, Special Agent in Charge,
David Branigan, F.B.I.

910
01:31:15,416 --> 01:31:18,442
Welcome to New York.
We're running N.Y.P.D. and
Agency response out of here...

911
01:31:18,520 --> 01:31:20,454
in coordination
with D.O.E.

912
01:31:20,522 --> 01:31:22,854
- Evacuation plans ?
- FEMA and National Guard are on alert.

913
01:31:22,924 --> 01:31:24,858
- What about NEST ?
- Energy has containment teams...

914
01:31:24,926 --> 01:31:27,861
on alert in Battery Park
awaiting instructions.

915
01:31:27,929 --> 01:31:29,863
We're running
casualty scenarios.

916
01:31:29,931 --> 01:31:33,389
Initial blast would throw 60 rads
of prompt radiation out three miles.

917
01:31:33,468 --> 01:31:38,531
That's most of lower Manhattan
and Queens-- 2.5 to 3 million
people, 50% survival rate.

918
01:31:38,606 --> 01:31:41,336
We're gonna need to monitor localized
wind patterns, and we're gonna need...

919
01:31:41,409 --> 01:31:43,343
radiation detectors,
ground and air.

920
01:31:43,411 --> 01:31:46,005
- Intel report from IFOR.
- Let me see that.

921
01:31:46,080 --> 01:31:49,516
All right, Vlado Mirich,
Bosnian-Serb, radical.

922
01:31:49,584 --> 01:31:53,680
Been missing for about a week. Father
fought with Tito. No wife or children.

923
01:31:53,755 --> 01:31:56,451
Has a half-brother who was
a classical pianist in Sarajevo.

924
01:31:56,524 --> 01:32:00,358
Mirich's been arrested three times
for smuggling and black-marketeering.

925
01:32:00,428 --> 01:32:02,794
- It's gotta be him.
- No, no, something doesn't fit.

926
01:32:02,864 --> 01:32:04,832
- What ?
- The man in the tape.

927
01:32:04,899 --> 01:32:06,958
He's no black-marketeer,
and he's not a nationalist.

928
01:32:07,035 --> 01:32:11,267
Remember, he said, ''l am a Serb,
a Croat and a Muslim.'' He's
holding everybody responsible.

929
01:32:11,339 --> 01:32:16,242
- This background doesn't fit.
- Sir, I'm checking all
incoming passenger manifests.

930
01:32:16,311 --> 01:32:20,645
I've got a V. Mirich on SwissAir
Flight 1204 from Zurich to Kennedy.

931
01:32:20,715 --> 01:32:22,649
- [ Devoe ] Arriving when ?
- Touchdown seven minutes ago.

932
01:32:22,717 --> 01:32:24,685
[ Devoe ] Call JFK.
Get Security. Send 'em a picture.

933
01:32:24,752 --> 01:32:26,720
- [ Kelly ] Reroute
to Kennedy Airport NEST.
- [ Ken ] Done.

934
01:32:26,788 --> 01:32:29,780
Excuse me.
Excuse me !

935
01:32:29,858 --> 01:32:32,793
Cover all the exits. Nobody gets out
of here. You understand me ?

936
01:32:32,861 --> 01:32:35,261
- Nobody gets out !
- [ Agent ] Who's Devoe ?

937
01:32:35,330 --> 01:32:37,890
- SwissAir Flight 1204, nonresidents.
- Station 20.

938
01:32:37,966 --> 01:32:39,900
This way.

939
01:32:43,705 --> 01:32:45,639
[ Kelly ]
He's not here.

940
01:32:45,707 --> 01:32:48,608
- He's not here !
- We got a possible identification
at desk seven.

941
01:32:48,676 --> 01:32:50,610
It's the far corner.

942
01:32:53,815 --> 01:32:55,783
Excuse me.

943
01:32:59,888 --> 01:33:01,788
Vlado Mirich ?

944
01:33:08,029 --> 01:33:10,497
Yes ?

945
01:33:13,701 --> 01:33:15,635
Who the hell is this ?

946
01:33:28,449 --> 01:33:32,408
- [ Speaking Serbian ]
- Uh-huh. All right.

947
01:33:32,487 --> 01:33:35,945
Passport's fake. Claims he bought it
on the street in Sarajevo.

948
01:33:36,024 --> 01:33:38,117
- He wants a lawyer.
- We've been able to detain eight men.

949
01:33:38,192 --> 01:33:41,684
Tried to enter today using passports
issued by the former Yugoslavia.

950
01:33:41,763 --> 01:33:44,732
- None matches your description.
- Where the hell is he ?

951
01:33:44,799 --> 01:33:47,529
- Even with the treaty signing ?
- That doesn't include the delegations.

952
01:33:47,602 --> 01:33:50,230
- The what ?
- They don't go through customs.

953
01:33:50,305 --> 01:33:54,002
- Give me that.
- Altogether, there must have
been a couple hundred of them.

954
01:33:55,843 --> 01:33:58,403
-[ Alex Trebek On TV ] ...Julius Caesar.
-[ Contestant ] Marcus Brutus.

955
01:33:58,479 --> 01:34:00,413
- [ Trebek ] Right.
- Half-brothers, 800.

956
01:34:00,481 --> 01:34:02,642
[ Trebek ]
Answer: Another Daily Double.

957
01:34:04,452 --> 01:34:06,477
[ Game Show Continues, lndistinct ]

958
01:34:31,846 --> 01:34:35,680
No, ma'am. Let me explain.
We are talking about a possible
terrorist situation.

959
01:34:35,750 --> 01:34:37,775
We need to detain
the entire delegation.

960
01:34:37,852 --> 01:34:41,788
These are diplomats, here as
guests of the State Department.
I can't order them around.

961
01:34:41,856 --> 01:34:45,553
- Then I need their names
and room numbers.
- We're looking for Vlado Mirich.

962
01:34:45,626 --> 01:34:48,618
- I need what floor they're on too.
- This isn't Vlado Mirich.

963
01:34:48,696 --> 01:34:52,188
This is Dusan Gavrich.
He's an alternate with
the Bosnian-Serb delegation.

964
01:34:52,266 --> 01:34:57,203
Their minister was assassinated
last week. Mr. Gavrich
is attending in his place.

965
01:34:57,271 --> 01:35:00,570
The brother.

966
01:35:14,756 --> 01:35:16,690
[ Beeping ]

967
01:35:20,862 --> 01:35:23,387
[ Firearms Cocking ]

968
01:35:25,299 --> 01:35:27,733
[ Poodle Wheezing ]

969
01:35:44,852 --> 01:35:46,979
[ Elevator Beeping ]

970
01:36:06,507 --> 01:36:08,634
Go. Go !

971
01:36:17,952 --> 01:36:22,048
Oh, shit. ''Diplomatic papers.''
They never even searched it.

972
01:36:23,858 --> 01:36:26,486
Still warm.

973
01:36:38,739 --> 01:36:40,673
Please. Move.

974
01:37:01,762 --> 01:37:05,061
.. [ Bach ]

975
01:37:30,324 --> 01:37:33,225
[ Gunshots, Screaming ]

976
01:37:36,364 --> 01:37:40,232
Nina ! Nina !

977
01:37:43,437 --> 01:37:47,533
- [ Gunshots, Pedestrians Screaming ]
- Nina !

978
01:37:54,482 --> 01:37:56,973
Nina ! Nina !

979
01:37:59,120 --> 01:38:03,056
[ Speaking Serbian ]

980
01:38:06,894 --> 01:38:10,159
[ Screaming ln Serbian ]

981
01:38:17,405 --> 01:38:19,339
[ Speaking Serbian ]
Help me !

982
01:38:20,741 --> 01:38:24,643
Help me !
Help my child !

983
01:38:24,712 --> 01:38:26,771
Please help me !

984
01:38:30,985 --> 01:38:33,954
[ Speaking Serbian ]

985
01:38:55,943 --> 01:38:59,242
[ Horns Honking ]

986
01:39:04,518 --> 01:39:06,986
East 44th Street.

987
01:39:09,090 --> 01:39:11,354
- D.O.E., you have anything yet ?
- Choppers are up.

988
01:39:13,094 --> 01:39:14,561
Couple of +2 spikes reported, but
nothing approaching target levels.

989
01:39:14,629 --> 01:39:16,563
The backpack's gonna be
leaking radiation.

990
01:39:16,631 --> 01:39:19,964
They should be able to locate him
within a three- to four-block area.

991
01:39:20,034 --> 01:39:22,525
Set up roadblocks here.
We're gonna close off Second Avenue.

992
01:39:22,603 --> 01:39:26,061
Funnel him down 43rd
to the U.N. We deploy snipers
between First and Second...

993
01:39:26,140 --> 01:39:28,074
- Command Center.
- and take him out.

994
01:39:28,142 --> 01:39:31,373
General, we have to close down
the east side of Second Avenue...

995
01:39:31,445 --> 01:39:35,973
from 55th to 42nd and the north side
of 42nd from Sixth to the river.

996
01:39:36,050 --> 01:39:38,917
- [ Kelly ] Let's go.
- [ Devoe ] We're gonna be
in position at the U.N.

997
01:39:38,986 --> 01:39:41,819
Instruct all field agents,
all snipers:

998
01:39:41,889 --> 01:39:44,084
Subject cannot be aware
of the hunt.

999
01:39:46,761 --> 01:39:48,695
[ Police Whistle Blowing ]

1000
01:39:54,168 --> 01:39:58,332
- [ Horns Honking, Whistle Blowing ]
- Move it.

1001
01:40:02,943 --> 01:40:07,573
Something big at U.N. today.
Traffic bad all morning.

1002
01:40:14,455 --> 01:40:16,514
[ Kelly ]
Chopper Hunter One, anything ?

1003
01:40:16,590 --> 01:40:21,618
- That's a negative.
- H.Q., Kelly. We're gonna work
our way south into the funnel.

1004
01:40:21,696 --> 01:40:24,688
Suggest stopping anyone
with a backpack north of 55th.

1005
01:40:24,765 --> 01:40:27,893
- [ Branigan ] Roger. How soon
will you get to the U.N. ?
- What are you talking about ?

1006
01:40:27,968 --> 01:40:31,096
This is
a national emergency.

1007
01:40:32,807 --> 01:40:36,208
- [ Pedestrians Shouting ]
- Get over here and spread 'em.

1008
01:40:36,277 --> 01:40:40,145
Hold it ! Up in the air ! Put your
hands on your head. Don't move.

1009
01:40:43,784 --> 01:40:46,275
Who are the fascists now ?
Du kleine Ficke !

1010
01:40:46,354 --> 01:40:48,822
[ Horns Honking ]

1011
01:40:48,889 --> 01:40:51,050
- [ Tires Squealing ]
- Come on !

1012
01:40:51,125 --> 01:40:52,820
Come on.

1013
01:40:52,893 --> 01:40:55,157
- [ Horns Honking ]
- [ Man ] Let's go !

1014
01:40:55,229 --> 01:40:57,322
- [ Siren Wailing ]
- Come on !

1015
01:41:10,745 --> 01:41:13,145
Okay, guys, let's move it out.
Go ! Go !

1016
01:41:14,415 --> 01:41:16,349
Come on.
Let's move it.

1017
01:41:16,417 --> 01:41:18,351
[ Whistling ]
Go !

1018
01:41:18,419 --> 01:41:21,547
[ Horns Honking, Drivers Shouting ]

1019
01:41:34,568 --> 01:41:38,163
- [ Siren Wailing ]
- [ Officer ] All right,
move back on the sidewalk.

1020
01:41:38,239 --> 01:41:40,605
- What the hell is this ?
- We have instructions to secure--

1021
01:41:40,674 --> 01:41:45,873
- It looks like Desert Storm !
Get these men outta here !
- He sees us, we're all dead.

1022
01:41:45,946 --> 01:41:48,881
- Colonel.
- N.Y.P.D. is shutting down
off-ramps to clear it.

1023
01:41:48,949 --> 01:41:50,917
- Where's the containment trucks ?
- It's gridlocked out there.

1024
01:41:50,985 --> 01:41:54,682
- Where are they ?
- [ Pilot ] We picked up
a diffused radiation source...

1025
01:41:54,755 --> 01:41:57,656
somewhere between Third and Second,
54th and 46th.

1026
01:41:57,725 --> 01:42:01,058
- Can you be more precise, D.O.E. ?
- Not at this altitude.

1027
01:42:01,128 --> 01:42:03,062
On my way.
You keep an open channel.

1028
01:42:03,130 --> 01:42:05,325
When we locate him, move out
with the NEST team.

1029
01:42:05,399 --> 01:42:07,333
[ Chattering ]

1030
01:42:20,981 --> 01:42:24,280
[ Helicopter Whirring ]

1031
01:42:30,391 --> 01:42:33,519
H.R.T. Command, put me direct
with your closest shooter.

1032
01:42:33,594 --> 01:42:35,892
- Hunter One, copy.
- Leader, this is One.

1033
01:42:35,963 --> 01:42:37,897
[ Devoe ]
Expect he's comin' your way, One.

1034
01:42:37,965 --> 01:42:40,593
[ Hunter One ]
Roger that. Do we have a green light ?

1035
01:42:40,668 --> 01:42:42,761
[ Devoe ]
Affirmative.

1036
01:42:55,516 --> 01:42:58,917
- [ Officer #1 ] Thank you.
- [ Officer #2 ]
Get outside the barriers, folks.

1037
01:42:58,986 --> 01:43:02,285
Good. That's good.

1038
01:43:02,356 --> 01:43:05,348
No, you may not walk that way.
Please turn around.

1039
01:43:05,426 --> 01:43:09,419
- Thank you. Round the barrier.
- Over to the left, please.

1040
01:43:09,497 --> 01:43:13,934
I think he's somewhere between
First and Second, probably below 46th.

1041
01:43:14,001 --> 01:43:16,731
All positions,
do you see target ?

1042
01:43:16,804 --> 01:43:18,999
No, sir.
Not me.

1043
01:43:20,107 --> 01:43:23,736
Come on.
Come to Papa.

1044
01:43:31,151 --> 01:43:35,315
This is Four. Target acquired.
Three hundred meters.

1045
01:43:35,389 --> 01:43:37,323
Not clean.
Too many friendlies.

1046
01:43:37,391 --> 01:43:39,882
Four, this is Leader.
Take the shot.

1047
01:43:39,960 --> 01:43:42,224
[ Hunter Four ]
There's a child, a family.

1048
01:43:42,296 --> 01:43:44,992
Acknowledged. Take the shot.

1049
01:43:46,367 --> 01:43:49,165
Shoot him.
Come on.

1050
01:43:50,404 --> 01:43:53,168
Four, this is Leader.
I repeat: Take the shot.

1051
01:43:54,508 --> 01:43:56,567
Take the shot !

1052
01:43:56,644 --> 01:43:59,738
Shoot him !
Take the shot !

1053
01:44:01,315 --> 01:44:04,773
- Oh, God.
- Goddamn it ! Somebody shoot him !

1054
01:44:07,821 --> 01:44:11,257
- [ Sighs ]
- This is One. I have target acquired.

1055
01:44:11,325 --> 01:44:16,285
Four hundred yards, inbound.
No shot. Should open at 43rd.

1056
01:44:16,363 --> 01:44:18,331
[ Siren Wailing ]

1057
01:44:21,335 --> 01:44:23,269
F.B.I. !

1058
01:44:27,141 --> 01:44:31,202
-I need to get the hell through.
-You and the rest of New York.
Take it easy, all right ?

1059
01:44:31,278 --> 01:44:33,542
Just get outta here.

1060
01:44:33,614 --> 01:44:37,448
Dispatch, this is 1501.
I need backup on 43rd Street...

1061
01:44:37,518 --> 01:44:39,611
as soon as
you can get it for me.

1062
01:44:39,687 --> 01:44:43,214
Leader, this is Hunter One.
Waiting for target to clear.

1063
01:44:44,625 --> 01:44:47,651
You with the backpack,
get your hands up.

1064
01:44:47,728 --> 01:44:50,720
- Get out of the way.
- Get your hands up.

1065
01:44:50,798 --> 01:44:53,198
I'm a diplomat
with the United Nations.

1066
01:44:55,936 --> 01:44:57,870
I must be allowed to pass.

1067
01:44:59,306 --> 01:45:01,365
Leader, I may have lost him.
He stopped.

1068
01:45:01,442 --> 01:45:04,536
- What ?
- He may have stopped.
He went behind some trees.

1069
01:45:04,612 --> 01:45:07,911
He's gotta be there.
Reacquire. Move if you have to.

1070
01:45:07,982 --> 01:45:12,146
- What've you got in
the backpack, buddy ? Cuffs.
- You got it.

1071
01:45:12,219 --> 01:45:15,211
- [ Gunshots ]
- [ Pedestrians Screaming ]

1072
01:45:15,289 --> 01:45:18,258
- Can you engage, Number One ?
- Negative, sir. Somebody shooting.

1073
01:45:18,325 --> 01:45:21,317
Corner of 43rd and Second.

1074
01:45:21,395 --> 01:45:23,590
Is he down ?

1075
01:45:26,400 --> 01:45:28,561
Is he down ?
ls he down ?

1076
01:45:28,636 --> 01:45:32,504
[ Hunter One ] Negative.
They're southbound, toward 42nd.

1077
01:45:32,573 --> 01:45:34,507
Stay in contact with the
containment trucks...

1078
01:45:34,575 --> 01:45:36,907
and have them ready to move
on my command.

1079
01:45:36,977 --> 01:45:40,413
- Where are you from ?
- Philadelphia.

1080
01:45:40,481 --> 01:45:42,415
Give me the keys.

1081
01:45:44,018 --> 01:45:48,614
[ Siren Wailing ]

1082
01:45:53,827 --> 01:45:57,695
Hey ! Out of the way !
D.O.E., you have him ?

1083
01:45:57,765 --> 01:46:00,632
He's eastbound on 42nd.

1084
01:46:03,037 --> 01:46:06,234
- Get out of the way !
- [ Siren Wailing ]

1085
01:46:13,347 --> 01:46:16,646
Go ! Make way !

1086
01:46:18,552 --> 01:46:21,419
[ Woman Screaming ]

1087
01:46:21,488 --> 01:46:23,547
Move it !

1088
01:46:33,033 --> 01:46:35,695
[ Cabbie ]
Hey, off o' the car !

1089
01:46:35,769 --> 01:46:38,135
[ Screaming ]

1090
01:46:44,511 --> 01:46:46,843
[ Speaking Serbian ]

1091
01:46:49,249 --> 01:46:52,241
Oh !

1092
01:47:13,841 --> 01:47:17,641
- East of Second, off 41st.
Give me backup now !
- He went down there !

1093
01:47:17,711 --> 01:47:20,043
- There !
- Stay behind me !

1094
01:47:31,425 --> 01:47:35,691
- [ Gasping ]
- Drop your weapon, and
show me your fuckin' hands.

1095
01:47:35,763 --> 01:47:37,993
We got him.
Alley off 41st.

1096
01:47:42,569 --> 01:47:44,696
[ Yelling Gleefully ]

1097
01:47:45,773 --> 01:47:48,503
[ Yelling ]

1098
01:47:53,714 --> 01:47:56,979
- [ Grunting ] You all right ?
- Yeah.

1099
01:48:08,762 --> 01:48:11,026
[ Gasping ]

1100
01:48:23,076 --> 01:48:26,842
[ Radio ] The signal just quit. You're
right there. He's gotta be indoors.

1101
01:48:26,914 --> 01:48:29,883
[ Panting ]
Oh, Vlado.

1102
01:48:29,950 --> 01:48:32,578
[ Speaking Serbian ]

1103
01:48:32,653 --> 01:48:35,520
- [ Woman ] I saw them !
- [ Man ] Up those stairs ! ln there !

1104
01:48:35,589 --> 01:48:38,854
[ Speaking Serbian ]

1105
01:48:42,196 --> 01:48:45,563
[ Door Opening, Bell Ringing ]

1106
01:48:45,632 --> 01:48:47,600
Move !
Move, move, move !

1107
01:48:47,668 --> 01:48:49,761
- [ Screaming ]
- Move ! Move !

1108
01:48:51,638 --> 01:48:54,368
- Move !
- [ Students Shouting, Screaming ]

1109
01:48:58,445 --> 01:49:02,176
- Anybody have him ?
- [ Radio ] Negative. Nothing to
the south end. Same to the north.

1110
01:49:02,249 --> 01:49:05,582
- D.O.E., what have you got ?
- Still picking up a diffused
energy source...

1111
01:49:05,652 --> 01:49:07,586
somewhere in the area.

1112
01:49:07,654 --> 01:49:10,452
We're circling back now.

1113
01:49:12,359 --> 01:49:14,293
He knows he'll never make it
to the U.N.

1114
01:49:14,361 --> 01:49:16,329
He doesn't have to.
He's got a nuclear weapon.

1115
01:49:16,396 --> 01:49:20,457
All he has to do is sit down behind a
Dumpster and take out half of Manhattan.

1116
01:49:20,534 --> 01:49:23,731
He doesn't wanna die behind a Dumpster.
He wants his death to mean something.

1117
01:49:23,804 --> 01:49:26,068
- [ Radio ] Still not getting
a clear reading.
- Keep circling.

1118
01:49:26,139 --> 01:49:29,768
Fan out. We've established
a new perimeter. He's gotta
be within 200 yards.

1119
01:49:29,843 --> 01:49:32,437
- Look for blood, door to door.
- [ Radio ] There's no sign, Colonel.

1120
01:49:32,512 --> 01:49:34,844
He probably
ducked into a building.

1121
01:49:34,915 --> 01:49:39,079
- Keep looking !
- Will continue circling
a six-block area.

1122
01:49:39,152 --> 01:49:43,748
.. [ Choir Singing ]

1123
01:49:43,824 --> 01:49:45,815
Devoe !

1124
01:49:45,893 --> 01:49:47,986
Listen.

1125
01:49:48,061 --> 01:49:52,998
.. [ Choir ]

1126
01:50:17,624 --> 01:50:20,457
[ Speaking Serbian ]

1127
01:50:20,527 --> 01:50:23,792
[ Shouting ln Serbian ]

1128
01:50:23,864 --> 01:50:27,322
- Go ! Go !
- [ Children Screaming ]

1129
01:50:27,401 --> 01:50:29,528
[ Priest ]
Hurry along. Come on. Come on.

1130
01:50:29,603 --> 01:50:33,801
- [ Screaming ]
- Father, take these children
out of here ! Move it !

1131
01:50:33,874 --> 01:50:37,310
[ Priest ] Come on, girls.
Quickly. Quickly, girls.

1132
01:50:45,252 --> 01:50:48,380
[ Faint Noise ]

1133
01:50:48,455 --> 01:50:51,219
Come on. Come on.
Give me your hand. Give me your hand.

1134
01:50:51,291 --> 01:50:54,055
Let's go. Go.

1135
01:50:54,127 --> 01:50:56,755
Go, go, go, go.

1136
01:50:59,967 --> 01:51:01,901
[ Indistinct Noise ]

1137
01:51:05,572 --> 01:51:07,938
[ Gasps ]

1138
01:51:10,877 --> 01:51:13,107
You cannot stop this.

1139
01:51:13,180 --> 01:51:15,114
Never !

1140
01:51:16,616 --> 01:51:18,550
Okay.

1141
01:51:19,853 --> 01:51:22,981
Okay, just,
just, just stay still.

1142
01:51:23,056 --> 01:51:25,456
Stay there.

1143
01:51:25,525 --> 01:51:27,584
Stay still.

1144
01:51:27,661 --> 01:51:29,595
It's okay.

1145
01:51:34,468 --> 01:51:36,595
You don't wanna die
like this.

1146
01:51:38,338 --> 01:51:42,934
Tell me about the bomb.
Is it on a trigger ?

1147
01:51:44,311 --> 01:51:47,109
Is it on a timer ?
ls it activated ?

1148
01:51:47,180 --> 01:51:49,410
Come on.
Talk to me.

1149
01:51:49,483 --> 01:51:51,474
- We can decide on a way out of this.
- [ Gasps ]

1150
01:51:51,551 --> 01:51:54,042
- [ Cocks Pistol ]
- No !

1151
01:51:56,456 --> 01:51:59,448
Who decided
for my wife ?

1152
01:52:00,727 --> 01:52:03,321
My child, murdered.
Huh ?

1153
01:52:04,765 --> 01:52:06,733
For what ?

1154
01:52:07,801 --> 01:52:09,735
For what ?

1155
01:52:13,040 --> 01:52:15,634
[ Whispering ]
For breathing ?

1156
01:52:15,709 --> 01:52:17,643
For smiling ?

1157
01:52:19,046 --> 01:52:21,378
And now, I am left.

1158
01:52:28,555 --> 01:52:31,115
Who decides for me ?

1159
01:52:31,191 --> 01:52:34,092
Mr. Gavrich,
what is it you want ?

1160
01:52:37,464 --> 01:52:41,025
[ Speaking Serbian ]

1161
01:52:41,101 --> 01:52:43,592
- I--
- I want it to be...

1162
01:52:44,704 --> 01:52:46,638
Iike it was.

1163
01:52:50,377 --> 01:52:53,107
Sir, it's not our war.

1164
01:52:57,417 --> 01:52:59,510
- It is now.
- No !

1165
01:53:03,523 --> 01:53:07,118
- Son of a bitch.
- Where the hell is NEST ?

1166
01:53:07,928 --> 01:53:09,520
- [ Beeping ]
- Get NEST in here !

1167
01:53:09,596 --> 01:53:13,191
- It's on a timer.
- All right, listen. The bomb's
on a timer, all right ?

1168
01:53:13,266 --> 01:53:16,463
Ken. Ken.
Where the hell are they ?

1169
01:53:16,536 --> 01:53:18,902
- I don't know. I'm on it.
- Ken, tell me NEST is here.

1170
01:53:18,972 --> 01:53:22,408
[ Ken ] Affirmative. We've cleared
43rd. They'll be there in four minutes.

1171
01:53:25,245 --> 01:53:28,078
They're not gonna make it.
They're not gonna make it !

1172
01:53:28,148 --> 01:53:31,515
All right.
Okay. You're gonna have to do this.

1173
01:53:31,585 --> 01:53:34,019
Understand ? Look at this.
Tell me what you see.

1174
01:53:34,087 --> 01:53:38,649
- Take a look at this
and tell me what you see !
- Yeah. Uh,

1175
01:53:38,725 --> 01:53:41,353
an SS18 primary
with a plutonium core.

1176
01:53:41,428 --> 01:53:46,365
A bomb inside a bomb. It has
a capacitor-relay detonator,
double pull, double throw.

1177
01:53:46,433 --> 01:53:49,766
Uh, the only way of knowing
is to open it up.

1178
01:53:49,836 --> 01:53:52,430
What ?

1179
01:53:54,407 --> 01:53:57,774
- What ?
- Let's move it into the chapel.
Get it off him. Get it off !

1180
01:53:57,844 --> 01:54:01,473
Hang on. We got a trip wire right here.
We're gonna move the man with the bomb.

1181
01:54:01,548 --> 01:54:03,516
All at once.
Here we go. Ready ? Go !

1182
01:54:03,583 --> 01:54:05,847
Let's go !
Let's go ! Careful !

1183
01:54:06,920 --> 01:54:09,946
Get the gate !

1184
01:54:10,023 --> 01:54:13,857
- Why in here ?
- It'll help contain the radiation.

1185
01:54:13,927 --> 01:54:18,387
You need to get out of the
church. Evacuate as many people
from this area as you can.

1186
01:54:19,833 --> 01:54:23,394
- Okay. I, uh, I need
something for the screws.
- Here.

1187
01:54:23,470 --> 01:54:25,802
- Anything. Quick !
- Go, go.

1188
01:54:35,682 --> 01:54:37,809
Devoe, get out of here.

1189
01:54:37,884 --> 01:54:41,581
Okay. I'll be in the truck.
[ Laughs ]

1190
01:54:45,825 --> 01:54:48,089
[ Gasping ]
Shit.

1191
01:55:03,877 --> 01:55:07,745
The plutonium core is surrounded
by explosive panels.

1192
01:55:07,814 --> 01:55:11,545
Uh, give me the knife.
I need the knife back.

1193
01:55:11,618 --> 01:55:13,643
If we can separate
one of the panels,

1194
01:55:13,720 --> 01:55:17,588
uh, we may be able to blow up
the outer bomb...

1195
01:55:17,657 --> 01:55:22,094
without the core
going to nuclear yield.

1196
01:55:22,162 --> 01:55:25,598
You're gonna blow this up.
You're gonna blow up the bomb ?

1197
01:55:25,665 --> 01:55:29,362
You know what you're doin', right ?
You've done somethin' like this before.

1198
01:55:29,436 --> 01:55:33,167
Defused stolen nuclear primaries
jerry-rigged by Pakistanis ?

1199
01:55:33,240 --> 01:55:35,299
No.

1200
01:55:38,044 --> 01:55:40,103
[ Beeping ]

1201
01:55:44,718 --> 01:55:46,845
Oh !
[ Gasping ]

1202
01:55:48,722 --> 01:55:51,714
- [ Blade Snapping ]
- Ah, damn !

1203
01:55:51,791 --> 01:55:54,282
All right.

1204
01:55:54,361 --> 01:55:57,524
Uh, I need your gun.
Give me the gun. I need the gun.

1205
01:55:57,597 --> 01:55:59,531
Go.

1206
01:56:02,068 --> 01:56:04,002
Easy, easy, easy, easy !

1207
01:56:04,070 --> 01:56:06,231
It's all right.

1208
01:56:06,306 --> 01:56:08,968
- [ Devoe ] Fourteen, thirteen, twelve,
- I know.

1209
01:56:09,042 --> 01:56:11,670
- eleven, ten,
- It won't let go !

1210
01:56:11,745 --> 01:56:13,975
- nine, eight--
- Move !

1211
01:56:14,047 --> 01:56:16,140
Come on ! Seven !
Come on ! Six, five !

1212
01:56:16,216 --> 01:56:18,377
Go, go, go, go !

1213
01:56:18,451 --> 01:56:21,045
[ Beeping ]

1214
01:56:21,121 --> 01:56:23,055
[ Rapid Beeping ]

1215
01:56:27,494 --> 01:56:30,486
[ Siren Wailing ]

1216
01:56:30,563 --> 01:56:33,828
Julia. Come here.
Come here. Are you okay ?

1217
01:56:33,900 --> 01:56:36,562
- [ Gasping ]
- Hey ! Are you okay ? Hey !

1218
01:56:36,636 --> 01:56:38,695
- Come here. Come here.
- [ Siren Wailing ]

1219
01:56:39,906 --> 01:56:42,898
Come here.
Hey.

1220
01:56:42,976 --> 01:56:46,139
- You okay ?
- I think so.

1221
01:56:46,212 --> 01:56:49,306
- [ Man ] Get in there with the ladder !
- All right.

1222
01:56:50,684 --> 01:56:52,618
[ Crying ]

1223
01:57:00,327 --> 01:57:03,728
Yeah. All right.
Hey, listen. You're okay.

1224
01:57:03,797 --> 01:57:05,890
All right ?

1225
01:57:05,965 --> 01:57:08,365
- You're okay.
- Sir, we need you to go with these men.

1226
01:57:08,435 --> 01:57:13,031
- Yeah. Go, go, go. Go.
- We have to get you to
a radiation checkpoint.

1227
01:57:13,106 --> 01:57:15,199
- Julia !
- I'm bleeding.

1228
01:57:15,275 --> 01:57:18,073
Julia.
Julia !

1229
01:57:20,780 --> 01:57:22,714
Julia !

1230
01:57:29,255 --> 01:57:32,190
[ Horn Blowing, Siren Wailing ]

1231
01:58:16,936 --> 01:58:19,404
So, they give you
any new medals ?

1232
01:58:19,472 --> 01:58:21,406
Yes, they did.

1233
01:58:21,474 --> 01:58:23,999
- Well, you worked very hard for them.
- Thank you.

1234
01:58:29,449 --> 01:58:32,577
So we've got kind of a tradition
over at military ops...

1235
01:58:32,652 --> 01:58:36,019
whenever combatants
come back from the field in one piece.

1236
01:58:36,089 --> 01:58:38,683
Uh, we buy each other
a beer.

1237
01:58:40,026 --> 01:58:43,052
- You made that up.
- Yes, I did.

1238
01:58:49,402 --> 01:58:53,862
Well, um,
I got ten more to go.

1239
01:58:58,011 --> 01:59:00,241
I'll wait.

1240
02:03:37,356 --> 02:03:40,917
Subtitles by
Captions, lnc. Los Angeles

